---
title: Tuscan-Spiced Chicken over Garlicky Tomato Spaghetti & Roasted Zucchini
description: We’re all about the simple pleasures in life, and this dinner is certainly one of them. You’ll place juicy slices of perfectly crusted pork tenderloin atop al dente spaghetti in a silky, garlicky sauce studded with bright morsels of tomato and roasted zucchini. Top with a shower of umami-rich Parmesan cheese for an extra-savory finishing touch, and you’ve got a weeknight dinner idea that’s simply pork-tacular.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/tuscan-pork-tenderloin-5003a43c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64dcffcbef3d37ebd500feb2.pdf
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Mediterranean
nutrition:
  calories: 690 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 72 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 49 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 530 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tuscan-spiced-chicken-64dcffcbef3d37ebd500feb2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise) lengthwise; slice into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces) into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Tuscan Heat Spice{½%tablespoon}, @salt{some}, and @pepper{some}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add pork and cook, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer pork to one side of a #baking sheet{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken or salmon for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 5-6 minutes per side, or cook salmon (skin sides down) until skin is crisp, 5-7 minutes, then flip and cook until cooked through, 1-2 minutes more. Turn off heat; transfer to a cutting board. Wipe out pan.

Toss zucchini with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper on opposite side of #baking sheet{} with pork.

Roast on top rack until pork is cooked through and zucchini is lightly browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Toss and roast zucchini as instructed (skip roasting chicken or salmon!).

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

When pasta has 5 minutes left, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add tomato and garlic; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Whisk in ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

> Use pan used for chicken or salmon here.

Add drained spaghetti, zucchini, half the @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, a splash of reserved pasta cooking water, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} to pan with sauce; toss to combine.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until pasta is thoroughly coated in sauce.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide spaghetti between plates; top with pork and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve.

> Slice chicken crosswise (skip slicing salmon!).

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.